olism to examine the women's own processes of self-reflection and criticism and the deeper fissures and asymmetries that undergird Japanese productivity and social order.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aAlcoholicsxFamily relationshipsxJapanxTokyo. 0aAlcoholicsxFamily relationshipszJapanzTokyo. 0aAlcoholics' spousesxJapanxTokyo. 0aAlcoholics' spouseszJapanzTokyo. 0aCodependencyxJapanxTokyo. 0aCodependencyzJapanzTokyo. 0aParents of drug addictsxJapanxTokyo. 0aParents of drug addictszJapanzTokyo. 0aSex rolexJapanxTokyo. 0aSex rolezJapanzTokyo. 0aSocial work with womenxJapanxTokyo. 0aSocial work with womenzJapanzTokyo. 0aWivesxJapanxTokyo. 0aWiveszJapanzTokyo. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Anthropology / Cultural & Social.2bisacsh  aalcohol.  aalcoholics.  aalcoholism.  acodependency.  acodependent relationships.  acultural issues.  adestructive behavior.  adrunkenness.  aenabling.  afamily life.  afamily relationships.  agender issues.  agender norms.  ajapan.  ajapanese culture.  ajapanese women.  amarriage.  amen and women.  amental health issues.  amiddle class.  anurturance.  apolitics of marriage.  apostwar japan.  apublic life.  asobriety.  asocial drinking.  asocial order.  asubstance abuse.  atokyo.  awives and mothers.  awives.  awomens roles.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013z978311069042240uhttps://doi.org/10.1525/978052093868740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520938687423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780520938687/original  a978-3-11-069042-2  University of California Press Backlist Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles